[1
Date: Sun 11 Feb 2001 11:30:45 +0100
From: Martin Haditsch, MD, PhD <martin.haditsch@travel-clinic.at>

Additional Comment
------------------
I just want to add that at the Austrian experts´ meeting on travel medicine
(April 2000) we also asked the industry to either provide the southern
hemisphere´s vaccine in Austria (or the northern hemisphere´s [in southern
hemisphere countries), or to extend the availability / shelf-life of the
regular vaccine (with the expectation of [providing some cross-immunity),
which actually expires [in June/July with the subsequent vaccine not being
available before September.
As far as I know one of the big hints for a global-acting vaccine is the
composition (derived from highest possible actuality [derived from the
currently circulating strains) which leads to a time gap (northern
hemisphere: September / southern hemisphere: January [according to the
information of Pasteur Merieux MSD).
Hopefully doctors and the (traveling) public will become aware of the
increasing risk of travel-related severe influenza infections with the
age-shift of travelers as a co-factor.
--
Martin Haditsch, MD, PhD
<martin.haditsch@travel-clinic.at>
