Date: Sat 10 Feb 2001 17:48:45 -0200
From: Fernando D.A. Pires <favila@matrix.com.br>

A Problem for Frequent Travellers
---------------------------------
Re the [global flu vaccine: I support you 100 per cent. I've talked about
it with a number of people, and I'm not convinced that the present policy
of vaccinating people at different times in both hemispheres is sound. What
about frequent travellers, airline crews, etc., who cross the Equator every
day and spread viruses everywhere?
--
Prof. Dr. Fernando Dias de Avila Pires
Instituto Oswaldo Cruz/UFSC
Rua Bico de Lacre, 79
